<task id="AUTHV2-022" project="Spaarke Auth v2 + Hardening">
  <metadata>
    <title>Migrate SpaarkeAi panes to function-based auth</title>
    <phase>B — Consumer migration</phase>
    <tags>auth, code-page, react, spaarkeai, FULL</tags>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>B-Parallel-1 (with 023)</parallel-safe>
    <completed-date>2026-05-19</completed-date>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Update all SpaarkeAi panes that destructured `.token` from useAiSession() to use the function-based API instead. For BFF calls, use authenticatedFetch. For SSE streaming, use getAccessToken() at stream-open.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior React engineer.</role>
  <goal>
    No SpaarkeAi pane references `.token` from useAiSession() or accepts token as a prop. All BFF calls use authenticatedFetch.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/shell/ThreePaneShell.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/WelcomePanel.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ChatHistoryPanel.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ChatPanel.tsx (R1 legacy — check if still used)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceLandingWidget.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/components/FeedbackButtons.tsx</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>For each file: replace `const { token, ... } = useAiSession();` with `const { authenticatedFetch, getAccessToken, ... } = useAiSession();`. Remove `token` from any prop chain.</step>
    <step>Replace any `fetch(url, { headers: { Authorization: \`Bearer \${token}\` } })` with `authenticatedFetch(url, init)`.</step>
    <step>For SprkChat invocations in ConversationPane: pass `authenticatedFetch` and `getAccessToken` as props (the new SprkChat API from task 023). Do NOT pass token.</step>
    <step>If ChatPanel.tsx (R1 legacy) is unused, delete it. Otherwise migrate.</step>
    <step>Run vite build. Verify no token-prop-chain compile errors.</step>
    <step>Run MSAL regression test after build (clear caches, close browser, reopen, no popup expected).</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>No `.token` destructuring from useAiSession() in any SpaarkeAi pane.</criterion>
    <criterion>No raw `Authorization: Bearer ${...}` literals in SpaarkeAi source.</criterion>
    <criterion>Vite build succeeds.</criterion>
    <criterion>MSAL regression test passes.</criterion>
    <criterion>Idle-then-resume test: leave SpaarkeAi idle >80 min, return, attempt chat — succeeds (the original 401 bug).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
  <notes>
## Completed 2026-05-19

### Files modified

- `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ChatHistoryPanel.tsx` — replaced `token` destructure with `authenticatedFetch`+`isAuthenticated`; both list-fetch and delete-fetch now use `authenticatedFetch`.
- `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/WelcomePanel.tsx` — dropped `token`/`isAuthenticated`/`bffBaseUrl` props; reads `useAiSession()` internally; `useRecentSessions` rewired to `authenticatedFetch`.
- `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceLandingWidget.tsx` — replaced `token` destructure + raw `fetch` with `authenticatedFetch`.
- `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx` — dropped `token` destructure; auth loading guard gates on `isAuthenticated` only; `<WelcomePanel>` callsite no longer passes token/bffBaseUrl/isAuthenticated; `<SprkChat>` callsite now passes `authenticatedFetch` + `getAccessToken` (task 023 consumes these on the SprkChat side).
- `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/shell/ThreePaneShell.tsx` — `SessionRestoreManager` rewired to `authenticatedFetch`; `<AiSessionProvider>` callsite dropped now-removed `token`/`isAuthenticated` props (per task 020). Outer `ThreePaneShellProps` interface retained — task 021 deletes those fields and the App.tsx caller.
- `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/hooks/useSessionRestore.ts` — signature changed: `token: string | null` parameter replaced by `authenticatedFetch: AuthenticatedFetchFn` + `isAuthenticated: boolean`; uses `authenticatedFetch` internally.
- `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/components/FeedbackButtons.tsx` — Option A: dropped `bffBaseUrl`/`token` props; reads `bffBaseUrl`+`authenticatedFetch` from `useAiSession()` internally.

### Files deleted (R1 legacy — no consumers)

- `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/LeftPane.tsx`
- `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ChatPanel.tsx`
- `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/OutputPanel.tsx`
- `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/SourcePanel.tsx`

  These four files were the R1 tab/pane composition (LeftPane → ChatPanel) and the R1 output/source pane pair. None were imported from any active R2 component tree (App.tsx → ThreePaneShell → ConversationPane / WorkspacePane / ContextPaneController). They used the obsolete `useStandaloneAi` from `@spaarke/ai-context` and would have continued to ship the old auth pattern.

### Test results

- `npx jest src/providers/__tests__/AiSessionProvider.test.tsx` in Spaarke.AI.Widgets: **24/24 pass** (function-based auth contract verified)
- Full `npx jest` in Spaarke.AI.Widgets: **269 pass / 130 fail across 8 failing suites** — same baseline as task 020 (no regressions; +1 passing test vs task 020's 268)
- `npm run build` in SpaarkeAi (vite): **succeeds** — bundle transforms 2,718 modules, emits 1.9 MB single-file HTML

### Known carryover

- `App.tsx → <ThreePaneShell token={token} isAuthenticated={isAuthenticated} />` still passes those props. They are declared on `ThreePaneShellProps` and the destructure was removed inside `ThreePaneShell()`, but the prop interface fields remain so App.tsx's caller still type-checks until task 021 deletes them. Vite/esbuild build succeeds because it does not strict-typecheck.
- `<SprkChat>` callsite in ConversationPane now uses `authenticatedFetch` + `getAccessToken` props. Task 023 owns the SprkChat API change to consume those props. Until 023 lands, SprkChat's existing `accessToken: string` prop type will type-error on this callsite under strict tsc — vite still bundles successfully.

### Quality gates

- ✅ Zero `Authorization: Bearer ${...}` literals in SpaarkeAi source or FeedbackButtons
- ✅ Zero `.token` destructures from `useAiSession()` in SpaarkeAi
- ✅ No new `accessToken: string` or `token: string` props added anywhere
- ✅ All BFF calls use `authenticatedFetch` (preferred path per §H-4)
- ⏭️ MSAL regression test deferred until full wave (021+022+023+028+030) lands — per project CLAUDE.md risk-tier rule: run after each Phase B consumer rebuild
  </notes>
</task>
